assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: The Hyakugo Bank, Ltd. provides various financial services to individual and corporate/ sole proprietor customers in Japan. The company offers ordinary, time, savings term, green, and foreign currency deposits; general account; credit and debit cards; certificate of deposit; safety deposit box; investment trust; government bonds; multi-purpose car, education, loan free, and loan reform loans, as well as student, card, housing, and other purpose loans. It also provides medical, cancer, disability, income protection, individual annuity, endowment, term, whole life, student, accident, overseas travel, and fire insurance; foreign remittance; inheritance related, currency exchange, direct debit reception, and fund transfer services. In addition, the company offers fund raising and business development support, fund settlement, convenience store storage, leasing consultation, management consulting consultation, system development consultation, and bills receivable management services, as well as night deposits, and corporation cards. The company was formerly known as 105th National Chartered Bank and changed its name to The Hyakugo Bank, Ltd. in 1897. The Hyakugo Bank, Ltd. was incorporated in 1878 and is headquartered in Tsu, Japan.
